<div class="post-date">Dec 22</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1021" title="Snow Day"> Snow Day</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>Well, I went in for my noon to 9 p.m. shift and they were talking about closing early at 5 p.m. Then after lunch the director said, forget this, we&#8217;re closing at 2 p.m. So two hours and 15 minutes into my shift, I was home again.</p>

	<p>Depending on road conditions, they&#8217;ll probably be closed again tomorrow. We&#8217;re scheduled to be closed on Christmas Eve and Christmas. It will indeed be interesting on Sunday when I return. I suspect there will be a mountain of books to check in.</p>

	<p>As noted the National Weather Service was talking seven inches of snow. Now they&#8217;re talking 15 inches here in our little rivertown. At this pace, I wonder if we&#8217;ll manage to get out of here Friday to visit family for the holidays. It shouldn&#8217;t be too bad as it&#8217;ll stop snowing tomorrow. By Friday afternoon the roads should be OK, but we&#8217;ll check road conditions first.</p>

	<p>We&#8217;re trying to figure out what to do with our newfound time. I should probably clean our apartment, but the urge to take a nap is also alluring.</p>

	<p>A snow plow just came around the corner. Darlene, looking out the window&#8230; &#8220;Oooh, even the snowplows are skidding. Please don&#8217;t hit our van.&#8221; It didn&#8217;t.</p>

	<p>It&#8217;s still snowing and life goes on.</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

